order_of_neg_one:
@[simp]
theorem order_of_neg_one [nontrivial R] : order_of (-1 : R) = if ring_char R = 2 then 1 else 2 :=
  by
  split_ifs
  · rw [neg_one_eq_one_iff.2 h, order_of_one]
  apply order_of_eq_prime
  · simp
  simpa [neg_one_eq_one_iff] using h
#align order_of_neg_one order_of_neg_one
neg_one_eq_one_iff:
theorem neg_one_eq_one_iff [nontrivial R] : (-1 : R) = 1 ↔ ring_char R = 2 :=
  by
  refine' ⟨fun h => _, fun h => @char_two.neg_eq _ (ring_char.of_eq h) 1⟩
  rw [eq_comm, ← sub_eq_zero, sub_neg_eq_add, ← Nat.cast_one, ← Nat.cast_add] at h
  exact ((Nat.dvd_prime Nat.prime_two).mp (ring_char.dvd h)).resolve_left char_p.ring_char_ne_one
#align neg_one_eq_one_iff neg_one_eq_one_iff

theorem multiset_sum_sq (l : Multiset R) : l.sum ^ 2 = (l.map (· ^ 2)).sum :=
